@node "WHATISIT" "What is CPSSpeed? "




CPSSpeed 1.0 is a Xenolink door for rating the speed at which an upload
occurred. It will show an ANSI bar chart and rate the transfer verbally.

I hacked this little door together in just over two hours, just to get the
transferring look-and-feel of a door I once ran in CNet.
@endnode

@node "INSTALLATION" "How can I install it?"


                           @{b}@{fg highlight}Installation is simple.@{ub}@{fg text}


1. Copy the directory "CPSSpeed" to your "DOORS:" assignment.

2. Edit your filemenu.scr like this:

CMD = "Whatever you use as an @{bg highlight}upload@{bg back} command"
   {
      Upload
      CliDoorNoBreak "Doors:CPSSpeed/CPSspeed ~11"
   }

CMD = "Whatever you use as a @{bg highlight}download@{bg back} command"
   {
      Download
      CliDoorNoBreak "Doors:CPSSpeed/CPSspeed ~11"
   }

3. Compile your filemenu.src with MENU filemenu.src

4. Wait for a user to transfer something, or transfer something using
   a node with nullmodem.device.

5. Enjoy!
@endnode

